  m_Name: sea urchin
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::FishData
  <fishName>k__BackingField: Black Sea Urchin
  <fishFact>k__BackingField: "Sea urchins are essentially a mouth on the ocean floor
    \u2014 their entire underside is a jaw-like structure called Aristotle's lantern,
    capable of scraping algae straight off rock. Those long, black spines aren't
    just defensive; they also help the urchin move and wedge itself into crevices.
    In healthy reefs, urchins are vital grazers \u2014 but when their numbers explode,
    they can turn a coral reef into a barren rock field. "
